  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Crush your <strong>cardamom pods</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [600ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Heat a pot with a matching lid, with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1676648255130-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1676648255130-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1676648255130-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1676648255130-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1676648255130-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add your <strong>ground turmeric </strong>and<strong> crushed cardamom pods</strong> to the pot and cook for 20 secs or until fragrant, then add your <strong>basmati rice</strong>, <strong>sultanas </strong>and<strong> vegetable stock </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked – this is your <strong>sultana rice</strong></p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676648258594-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676648258594-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676648258594-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676648258594-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676648258594-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, top, tail, peel and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Cut your<strong> lemon[s] </strong>into wedges</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks</p><p>Strip your<strong> mint leaves </strong>from their stems and chop them finely, discarding the stems</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676648262119-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676648262119-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676648262119-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
