          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1676648394130-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1676648394130-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the fish is cooking, add the <strong>grated carrot</strong>, <strong>sliced spring onion</strong>,<strong> nigella seeds</strong>,<strong> remaining chopped mint </strong>and <strong>remaining chopped coriander </strong>to a large bowl</p><p>Add the juice of <strong>half</strong> your<strong> lemon[s]</strong>,<strong> </strong>2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]<strong> </span>olive oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and mix it all together – this is your <strong>Indian-style carrot slaw</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1676648477087-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1676648477087-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1676648477087-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1676648477087-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1676648477087-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> curried hake</strong> over the <strong>sultana rice</strong> with the <strong>Indian-style carrot slaw</strong> to the side</p><p>Top the fish with the<strong> tomato salsa </strong>and garnish with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lemon wedges</strong></p><p>Tip: Watch out for the cardamom pods!</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
